metadata.name: Try/Hatch #73
metadata.description:
In full screen view, click on the graphic to download plottable SVG in A3 format.

The color palette used in here is supposed to represent 25 Stabilo Point fineliners. The color values don't come from any official specification, though.

Every minted edition consists of 3 color layers:

- black-ish (pen number 46) with constant hatching distance
- two color layers with randomly chosen color and distance values

If you have a pen plotter, you can jump straight into making a physical drawing. Please be aware, that physical plot might differ from the digital version due to the pen and paper color differences.

Each group ID consists of an index, a HEX color value, and a Stabilo Point pen color number. In Inkscape, just convert groups to layers, and you can start to plot (probably the best experience with AxiDraw A3 pen plotter).

If you don't own a plotter or you want a regular print, simply convert your SVG to raster format.

License: CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/ - @jakub_antolak

metadata.name: Kinetograms #212
metadata.description:
Each Kinetogram traces the movement of a number of simple shapes constrained within a single cell or a grid of cells. Forces are applied to the shapes in the form of attraction, gravity or shaking.

Some Kinetograms are partially or completely reflected, vertically or horizontally, some with chromatic replacement.

The aspect ratio is 3:4. The palettes are predominantly based on found textile patterns.

Press 's' to save a png image. Press 'e' to redraw and export a 4K png image. Note that drawing and physical simulation takes some time.

For interactive use, press 't' to tilt the board and 'c' to clear the board.

Written in p5.js with 2D physical simulation using Matter.js. Developed in and optimized for Chrome.

metadata.name: Melody #2
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

The iterations are best viewed in Live Mode.

'Melody' explores color, space and geometry... with a touch of optical illusion thrown in!

It is called 'Melody' because each image resembles notes on a sheet of music.

In live mode:
Click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1800x2400px PNG.

metadata.name: Возвышение #32
metadata.description:
Возвышение (Eng.: Elevation) is the next step of my study of Suprematism, textures and colours, partially inspired by Lazar Khidekel works. 
The work depicts the superiority of the simplest geometric forms and colours over everything else.

——————

Rendering takes around 20-30 seconds at 60 fps, might take longer on older devices.
Press [Arrow Up / Down] to increase / decrease drawing speed.
Press [1…6] to change an image resolution up to 10k.
Press [S] after the image is rendered to save it.

metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #81
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. “The Bugged Tree”’s code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren’t under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there’s a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.name: Grid Return #4
metadata.description:
With "Grid Return" (Sept. 2022), I revisit the conceptual territory of my genesis work, "Grid Meditations" (Jan. 2022).

The four tenets of the Grid that I proclaimed eight months ago still ring true for me today:

1. The grid is the ultimate tool of abstraction.

2. The grid rejects any imitation of depth.

3. The grid exposes the true nature of the canvas as a two-dimensional surface.

4. The grid both imposes order and allows for the legibility of disorder.

metadata.name: MetaRack #12
metadata.description:
MetaRack is a generative modular synthesizer capable of producing random yet nice sounding patches. MetaRack is written from scratch, with pure sample-by-sample processing and no 3rd party libraries were used for audio handling. Also no samples or prepared audio files were used in this project, everything you hear is generated on-the-fly. The only library involved in MetaRack is p5js which is used for drawing graphical elements.

MetaRack is also a part of a bigger project - we are working on a gallery based on fxhash ecosystem which will allow collectors to connect and arrange their tokens, probably producing derivative NFTs. When launched, MetaRack token holders will receive an exclusive module collection. For more info please read the article https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/metarack-modular-synthesizer

Interface:
S - save
L - load
SHIFT - change modulation depth while rotating a knob

metadata.name: Burn Garden #2
metadata.description:
Burn Garden is a generative art work representing plants that grow as if they were fire. The plants burn different kinds of fruits that are a metaphor for NTF tokens that are created. The tokens become lighter, evolve, transfer and start floating in the sky as if they were pushed up by the hot air of the combustion
-	Hit ‘s’ to save a hi res (3072x3072) png file

metadata.name: Flustels #48
metadata.description:
Fully generative artwork in crayoning style.

The model uses Perlin noise map multiplied by map with flowers.
Each flower generated randomly with circles and ellipses. 

Each token is 100% unique.

Traits:
- 20 color palettes;
- 5 compositions;
- 9 background styles;
- 2 brush weights.

Press 's' to save .png with resolution 2000px * 2000px.

Renders fastest in Chrome browser.

Made with p5js, math and love by @ivposure
